ics that shaped them. She charts how climate change discussions align with US fears of China's ascendancy and the related demise of the American Century, and she considers the motives of financial and political capital for eco-city and ecological development supported by elite power structures in the UK and China. Fantasy Islands shows how ineffectual these efforts are while challenging us to see what a true eco-city would be.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSustainable developmentzChinazShanghai. 0aUrban ecology (Sociology)zChinazShanghai. 0aUrban ecology (Sociology)zUnited States. 0aUrban renewalzChinazShanghai. 70(DE-601)10415151X0(DE-588)4138354-0aLebensstil2gnd 70(DE-601)1043768640(DE-588)4120658-7aLebensraum2gnd 70(DE-601)1044349100(DE-588)4043207-5aÖkologie2gnd 70(DE-601)1047201070(DE-588)4241423-4aWohnraum2gnd 70(DE-601)1061538970(DE-588)4056730-8aStadtentwicklung2gnd 70(DE-601)1313093820(DE-588)4326464-5aNachhaltigkeit2gnd 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh  aasian history.  achina.  achinese government.  aclimate change.  aclimate.  adiplomacy.  adongtan.  aeco city.  aeco desire.  aeco technology.  aecocritical cultural studies.  aecological development.  aelite power.  aenvironment.  aenvironmental degradation.  aenvironmental studies.  aeurope.  afinancial capital.  aglobal economic change.  aglobal warming.  aglobalization.  ainternational power.  aleading global factory.  anational power.  apacific rim politics.  aphenomenon.  apolitical capital.  apolitics.  asociology.  atechnology.  aunited states of america.  aurban planning.  aworld.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052026248540uhttps://d